iate contracts to close deals. Build and maintain a pipeline of clients, and take responsibility for the relationship throughout all stages. Lead and manage a team of Sales Representatives. Conduct quarterly business reports presenting relevant information to show metrics and possible growth opportunities. Use client relationship software (CRM) to analyze user data and keep track of current partnerships. Keep abreast of industry related knowledge and developments, and conduct research to identify new markets and customer needs. Improve sales strategies by identifying risks and inefficiencies, and implement appropriate solutions. Represent Paxful in a professional manner at industry events and conferences, and be an ambassador for our brand. Travel up to 30% of the time locally and nationally. Perform other duties as assigned. Basic Qualifications: Minimum of 8 years of experience working in the sales/business development field, preferably in financial technology. Excellent written and verbal communication. Well developed interpersonal skills with the ability to build and maintain relationships. Ability to deal with ambiguity and shifting priorities. Strong interest in cryptocurrencies. Mastery in CRM, Microsoft Excel, Google Applications and sales analytics softwares. Preferred Qualifications: Bachelor\u2019s degree in Finance, Business, Technology, Marketing, or related field. Experience working in cryptocurrency industry in a relevant role. Startup or entrepreneurship experience. Perks: Accessible office in the Financial District Flexible hours Competitive salary, with the option of payment in bitcoin Premium covered healthcare insurance, including dental and vision Catered lunch and dinner daily Gym membership of your choice Sponsored sports nutrition and health-related activities Paid maternity/paternity leave including a special one-time bonus to support newborn Commuter benefits Training and professional development resources Paid company retreats Skills sales